description.p:
The sensor in these devices comprises in particular:
a food temperature transducer;
connection means to connect with the control means;
an interface circuit between the transducer and the connection means;
an external case that protects the elements that it contains.

Other preferential characteristics of the temperature monitoring device according to the invention are:
the sensor further comprises an electrical power supply for the entire sensor operating autonomously, such as an electric cell or rechargeable battery, installed in the case;
the cover is made of silicone;
the autonomous power supply of the sensor can operate up to a temperature of approximately 130°C (266° F);
the autonomous power supply of the sensor can operate from a temperature of approximately -40°C (-40°F);
the autonomous power supply of the sensor is a non saline and non alkaline electric cell;
the autonomous power supply of the sensor is a thionyl lithium electric cell;
the case is electrically conductive and the sensor further comprises an electric power switch-of means if the sensor in not in contact with the said matter, the power switch-off means being sensitive to the conductivity of the said matter;
the transmitter circuit transmits electromagnetic waves by bursts;
the hermetic case is made of a single piece;
the case is composed of several fitted parts that can be disassembled;
assembly means of two parts of the hermetic case are metallic and create an electric contact to' operate the sensor;
the case is laid out so as to facilitate the inserting of the sensor into the said matter;
the sensor further comprises an electromagnetic wave transmitting aerial laid out so as to further compose a means of gripping;
the aerial is covered with an electrical insulating material;
the aerial is covered with silicone foam;
the device further comprises a control unit to control the thermal data transmitted by the sensor via electromagnetic way, this control unit comprising:
a receiver for the type of electromagnetic waves transmitted by the sensor;
a micro-controller capable of controlling the thermal data in electromagnetic form received from the sensor by the receiver, and of transmitting at least a part of it to a user interface;
the user interface comprising transmission means of the thermal data in a form understandable to the user of the device.
The control unit further comprises a memory capable of storing thermal data, and the micro-controller is capable of processing the thermal data received from the sensor in accordance with this thermal data;
the user interface comprises an alarm, the thermal data stored in the memory corresponds to a temperature threshold, and the micro-controller triggers the alarm if the temperature detected by the sensor its greater than the temperature threshold;
the user interface comprises means that allow the user to enter data into the memory;
the interface means comprises an alarm, and the micro-controller triggers the alarm if it does not receive any electromagnetic waves over a pre-set duration of time or if it does not receive one or several thermal data informations it should have received.

In reference to figure 1, an example of a wireless temperature sensor 10 is represented according to the invention comprising:
a temperature transducer 8, designed to read the temperature within matter that is at least partly of water;
an electric circuit 7 transmitting electromagnetic waves, electrically connected to the temperature transducer 8, comprising a converter of electric signals coming from the transducer 8 in the form of electromagnetic-type signals;
an electric power supply 6, electrically energising all of the electric elements of the sensor 10, and operating autonomously or practically autonomously;
a hermetic case designed to be fitted with the entire electrical system comprising a temperature transducer 8, the electric circuit 9 and the autonomous power supply 6.

The description of the application of the sensor 10 to the monitoring of a cold chain is generally speaking similar to that of the sensor 10 to the monitoring of heat, except for the following points:
the operating temperature of the sensor is extended to approximately -40°C;
the sensor 10 is not inserted into the food but is adjacent to it, the temperatures of the food, of the sensor 10 and of the casing being substantially equivalent;
the temperature of the refrigerated casing does not compromise to working order of the sensor, which resists in the long term;
the commutation system described above, which allows the sensor 10 to be supplied with electricity when it is inside the food, can therefore not operate in cold conditions; thus, the sensor continually transmits, via bursts, and the fastening of the case of the sensor 10 always renders the transmitter circuit 7 and the temperature transducer 8 live;
the silicone foam protects the user from skin bonding against the metallic aerial 9, thus allowing the sensor to be handled without any risks.

Thus, according to the invention, other types of alarm can be envisaged such as, for example:
an activating of the control unit 20 prior to the sensor 10 being inserted into the food triggers an alarm;
a disappearing of the electromagnetic link after a pre-set time period or the absence of a pre-set number of bursts triggers an alarm;
the draining of the autonomous power supply 6 of the sensor 10 triggers an alarm as it interrupts the transmission;
the recording of a temperature that is out with the authorised limits for the efficient operating of the sensor 10 triggers the recording to the memory of the monitoring case and a message appears on the display of the latter.

claim.claim-text:
Temperaturkontrollvorrichtung eines Gegenstands (10), der zumindest teilweise aus Wasser besteht, wie beispielsweise Nahrung, welcher einen kabellosen Temperatursensor aufweist, mit:
- einem Temperaturmessfühler (8) des Gegenstands;
- einem elektromagnetischen Wellenübertragungskreislauf (7), welcher elektrisch mit dem Temperaturmessfühler verbunden ist, mit einem Umwandler von elektronischen Signalen, welche von dem Messfühler stammen, in Signale elektromagnetischen Typs;
- einem luftdichten und hoch wärmeleitenden Gehäuse (2), welches derart ausgebildet ist, dass es mit allen elektronischen Systemen ausgestattet werden kann, die den Temperaturmessfühler und den Übertragungskreislauf aufweisen;
wobei der Sensor derart ausgelegt ist, dass der Temperaturmessfühler nahe am Übertragungskreislauf angeordnet ist, und dadurch eine kompakte Einheit ausbildet;

wobei der Sensor eine innerhalb des Gehäuses angeordnete elektronische Zelle (6) zur elektrischen Energieversorgung des gesamten, autonom arbeitenden Sensors aufweist;

wobei der Sensor weiterhin eine elektromagnetische Wellenübertragungsantenne (9) aufweist, welche derart ausgelegt ist, dass sie weitere Halteelemente ausbildet,

dadurch gekennzeichnet, dass

die elektrische Zelle von dem Überträger und dem Messfühler beabstandet angeordnet ist, so dass sie außerhalb des Gegenstandes bleibt, wenn der Sensor in den Gegenstand eingeführt wird, und wobei die elektrische Zelle gegen Hitze durch eine Abdeckung aus wärmeisolierendem Material (11) geschützt ist, wodurch ein Hitzeschild ausbildet wird.

System zum Kontrollieren einer Temperatur eines Gegenstands, der zumindest teilweise aus Wasser besteht, wie beispielsweise Nahrung, welcher in einem Ofen platziert werden soll, mit:
einer Temperaturkontrollvorrichtung nach einem der vorangehenden Ansprüche; und
einer Kontrolleinheit, welche unabhängig vom Zustand des Ofens ist, und welche die thermischen Messdaten, welche von dem Sensor auf elektromagnetische Art und Weise übertragen werden, kontrolliert, wobei die Kontrolleinheit aufweist:
- einen Empfänger für die Art von elektromagnetischen Wellen, welche von dem Sensor übertragen werden;
- einen Mikrokontroller, welcher in der Lage ist, die thermischen Messdaten in elektromagnetischer Form, welche über den Empfänger von dem Sensor empfangen werden, zu kontrollieren und zumindest einen Teil davon auf eine Benutzeroberfläche zu übertragen;
wobei die Benutzeroberfläche Übertragungselemente der thermischen Messdaten in eine dem Benutzer der Vorrichtung verständliche Form aufweist.

Temperature monitoring device (10) to of a matter that is at least partly of water, such as food, comprising a wireless temperature sensor comprising:
• a temperature transducer (8) of the said matter;
• an electromagnetic wave transmitter circuit (7) electrically connected to the temperature transducer, comprising a converter of electric signals coming from the transducer to electromagnetic type signals;
• a hermetic and highly thermal conductive case (2) designed to be fitted, with all of the electric system comprising the temperature transducer and the transmitter circuit;
the sensor being laid out so that the temperature transducer is located near to the transmitter circuit, thereby forming a compact unit;

the sensor comprising an electric cell (6) for supplying electric power to the whole sensor that operates autonomously, placed inside the case; the sensor further comprising an electromagnetic wave transmitting aerial (9) laid out so as to further constitute means of gripping; characterized in that

the electric cell is distant from the transmitter and the transducer so that it remains outside the matter when the sensor is inserted into the matter, and in that the electric cell is protected against heat by a cover of thermal insulating material (11), thus forming a thermal shield.

System for monitoring a temperature of a matter that is at least partly of water, such as food, intended to be placed in an oven, comprising:
a temperature monitoring device according to any of the previous claims ; and
a control unit independent from the oven behaviour, and controlling the thermal data transmitted from the sensor by electromagnetic way, this control unit comprising :
• a receiver for the type of electromagnetic waves transmitted by the sensor;
• a micro-controller capable of controlling the thermal data in electromagnetic form received from the sensor by the receiver, and of transmitting at least a part of it to a user interface;
the user interface comprising transmission means of the thermal data in a form understandable to the user of the device.

Dispositif de surveillance de la température (10) d'une matière qui est au moins partiellement constituée d'eau, telle qu'un aliment, comprenant un capteur de température sans fil, comprenant :
- un transducteur de température (2) de ladite matière ;
- un circuit émetteur d'ondes électromagnétiques (7) connecté électriquement au transducteur de température, comprenant un convertisseur des signaux électriques provenant du transducteur en signaux de type électromagnétique ;
- un boîtier hermétique et à haute conductivité thermique (2) conçu pour loger l'ensemble du système électrique comprenant le transducteur de température et le circuit émetteur ;
le capteur étant disposé de telle sorte que le transducteur de température se trouve à proximité du circuit émetteur, formant ainsi une unité compacte ;

le capteur comprenant une pile électrique (6) pour alimenter en énergie électrique l'ensemble du capteur qui fonctionne de façon autonome, placé à l'intérieur du boîtier ;

le capteur comprenant en outre une antenne d'émission d'ondes électromagnétiques (9) disposée de sorte à constituer en outre des moyens de préhension ;

caractérisé en ce que

la pile électrique est distante de l'émetteur et du transducteur de telle sorte qu'elle reste à l'extérieur de la matière lorsque le capteur est inséré dans la matière, et en ce que la pile électrique est protégée contre la chaleur par un couvercle en matériau thermo-isolant (11), formant ainsi un bouclier thermique.

Système pour surveiller une température d'une matière qui est au moins partiellement constituée d'eau, telle qu'un aliment, conçu pour être placé dans un four, comprenant :
un dispositif de surveillance de la température selon l'une quelconque des revendications précédentes ; et
une unité de contrôle indépendante du comportement du four, et contrôlant les données thermiques émises depuis le capteur d'une manière électromagnétique, cette unité de contrôle comprenant :
- un récepteur pour le type d'ondes électromagnétiques émises par le capteur ;
- un microcontrôleur capable de contrôler les données thermiques sous forme électromagnétique reçues du capteur par le récepteur, et de transmettre au moins une partie de ces données à une interface utilisateur ;
l'interface utilisateur comprenant des moyens d'émission des données thermiques sous une forme facile à comprendre par l'utilisateur du dispositif.
